1
00:00:00,790 --> 00:00:04,950
Do you think that love is an illusion?

2
00:00:04,950 --> 00:00:07,980
Love is an instinct.

3
00:00:07,980 --> 00:00:12,380
There, just now. The person who came to your mind.

4
00:00:12,380 --> 00:00:14,510
That's instinct.

5
00:00:19,950 --> 00:00:21,510
Sorry.

6
00:01:05,110 --> 00:01:07,100
You're having hiccups?

7
00:01:20,160 --> 00:01:21,680
Erm...

8
00:01:23,140 --> 00:01:25,020
I just want to confirm something.

9
00:01:25,020 --> 00:01:26,510
Go ahead.

10
00:01:27,760 --> 00:01:31,330
What just happened was due to romantic interest, right?
If so, I...

11
00:01:31,330 --> 00:01:33,220
No, it wasn't.

12
00:01:33,220 --> 00:01:36,640
That... was purely a reflex.

13
00:01:36,640 --> 00:01:39,550
- Reflex?
- Right. Spinal reflex, they call it.

14
00:01:39,550 --> 00:01:44,770
You know, like when parrots peck with their beaks,
or dolphins nuzzle.

15
00:01:44,770 --> 00:01:47,410
It was a reflex, with no other meaning to it.

16
00:02:05,830 --> 00:02:06,950
Yes?

17
00:02:06,950 --> 00:02:09,310
Good news, Mr. Shirosaki!

18
00:02:09,310 --> 00:02:11,030
Good news?

19
00:02:13,070 --> 00:02:16,880
Mr. Shirosaki! You're here too, Ms. Hanamura.

20
00:02:16,880 --> 00:02:19,970
Did you both meet each other during your break, sir?

21
00:02:19,970 --> 00:02:22,020
- No, I...
- I came for Sakura...

22
00:02:22,020 --> 00:02:25,120
Don't worry, I was just casually asking.

23
00:02:25,120 --> 00:02:27,730
But it's nice, isn't it?

24
00:02:27,730 --> 00:02:31,880
Meeting each other in between breaks,
secretly going out together...

25
00:02:31,880 --> 00:02:34,040
I went through this before, too.

26
00:02:34,040 --> 00:02:37,120
Once upon a time, I dropped my glove at a ski resort,

27
00:02:37,120 --> 00:02:39,980
and the one who picked it up for me is now my husband.

28
00:02:39,980 --> 00:02:41,580
At the mountain lodge,

29
00:02:41,580 --> 00:02:46,130
we'd blow on toasted marshmallows
while watching the fire on the stove...

30
00:02:48,830 --> 00:02:51,870
- I guess that's irrelevant to you.
- No, that was lovely.

31
00:02:51,870 --> 00:02:55,150
In any case, it's great that you're back. Ms. Yuka is here.

32
00:02:59,050 --> 00:03:01,110
A sponsor?

33
00:03:01,110 --> 00:03:04,050
That's right. This must be fate.

34
00:03:04,860 --> 00:03:07,520
Kai, you're back. Hello to you too, Aiko.

35
00:03:07,520 --> 00:03:08,900
I heard you've found a sponsor?

36
00:03:08,900 --> 00:03:10,330
For the animal shelter?

37
00:03:10,330 --> 00:03:13,150
That's right. Take a look.

38
00:03:13,150 --> 00:03:14,950
[Renovation of Block B, Animal Shelter Sincere Home
- Request for Urgent Support]

39
00:03:14,950 --> 00:03:19,680
- You see...
- The topic came up when we were celebrating a pup's birthday.

40
00:03:19,680 --> 00:03:22,450
Gao, congrats on your eighth birthday!
[Happy Birthday, Gao]

41
00:03:22,450 --> 00:03:25,310
- Happy birthday!
- Happy birthday!

42
00:03:26,020 --> 00:03:28,760
This is from our boss.

43
00:03:28,760 --> 00:03:30,600
It's a toothbrush set and some snacks.

44
00:03:30,600 --> 00:03:32,950
Thank you for the gifts.

45
00:03:33,880 --> 00:03:34,950
What's this?

46
00:03:34,950 --> 00:03:36,910
It's a pet rescue card.
[Owner's name: Hiroshi Teshima, Pet's name: Gao]

47
00:03:36,910 --> 00:03:41,270
You can write down what to do with your pet
if anything happens to you.

48
00:03:41,270 --> 00:03:43,920
Just in case, we have also included our shop's contact number.

49
00:03:43,920 --> 00:03:47,920
Thank you so much for making sure Gao is well taken care of.

50
00:03:50,220 --> 00:03:53,860
Turns out that owner's son is an executive
at an insurance company.

51
00:03:53,860 --> 00:03:56,750
There are all kinds of pet insurance these days, right?

52
00:03:56,750 --> 00:03:59,760
They cover doctor visits, hospitalization, surgeries,

53
00:03:59,760 --> 00:04:02,610
dental checkups, and even pet hotel discounts.

54
00:04:02,610 --> 00:04:04,760
So as a company newly offering pet insurance,

55
00:04:04,760 --> 00:04:07,640
they're interested in helping fund the shelter.

56
00:04:07,640 --> 00:04:10,150
I haven't seen you this chatty before, Kana.

57
00:04:10,150 --> 00:04:12,620
Sorry, I was so excited, I got carried away.

58
00:04:12,620 --> 00:04:15,980
Of course you'd be thrilled. It's a huge donation!

59
00:04:15,980 --> 00:04:17,930
We're talking about hundreds of millions here.

60
00:04:17,930 --> 00:04:21,760
That's right. All for the ideal pet town
that Mr. Shirosaki envisioned.

61
00:04:21,760 --> 00:04:24,690
To make it work,
we'd need 300 million for renovations, for starters.

62
00:04:24,690 --> 00:04:28,410
Operations-wise, there's personnel costs, utilities,
food and medical expenses.

63
00:04:28,410 --> 00:04:30,890
That adds up to 1.2 billion yearly.

64
00:04:30,890 --> 00:04:33,140
And that'll all be paid for by the insurance company?

65
00:04:33,140 --> 00:04:35,180
Of course, making profits is their goal,

66
00:04:35,180 --> 00:04:38,820
but they also agree with Ms. Yuka and Mr. Shirosaki's vision,
and are eager to help.

67
00:04:38,820 --> 00:04:41,020
That sounds really wonderful, doesn't it?

68
00:04:41,020 --> 00:04:42,280
- Right?
- Yeah.

69
00:04:42,280 --> 00:04:45,610
That's really wonderful!

70
00:04:45,610 --> 00:04:48,510
Could I hear more about this insurance company?

71
00:04:48,510 --> 00:04:51,460
Right. We should confirm their credibility, just in case.

72
00:04:52,070 --> 00:04:54,570
We have looked into it, of course.

73
00:04:54,570 --> 00:04:56,260
I've also consulted an expert on this.

74
00:04:56,260 --> 00:04:58,880
They're definitely a trustworthy company with good ethics.
[Premium - Pet Insurance]

75
00:04:58,880 --> 00:05:02,600
Indeed, this is a listed company with stable performance.
[Top pet insurance provider for 15 years]

76
00:05:02,600 --> 00:05:06,100
Our law firm has also liaised with them several times.

77
00:05:06,100 --> 00:05:09,700
- So we're not far from our dream.
- Yeah.

78
00:05:09,700 --> 00:05:12,240
We can finally kick things off.

79
00:05:12,240 --> 00:05:14,090
High-five, Mr. Shirosaki.

80
00:05:15,820 --> 00:05:17,880
Mr. Shirosaki.

81
00:05:17,880 --> 00:05:19,650
Mr. Shirosaki.

82
00:05:19,650 --> 00:05:21,180
Mr. Shirosaki.

83
00:05:26,500 --> 00:05:29,300
- Congratulations.
- Thank you.

84
00:05:29,300 --> 00:05:31,810
Mr. Shirosaki, let's go out for drinks today.

85
00:05:31,810 --> 00:05:33,440
That's right. To celebrate.

86
00:05:33,440 --> 00:05:35,080
- I'm joining in.
- Me too!

87
00:05:35,080 --> 00:05:36,770
But I'm on the night shift today.

88
00:05:36,770 --> 00:05:40,260
People who love drinking will always find a way to drink, right?

89
00:05:40,260 --> 00:05:41,460
Join us too, Ms. Aiko.

90
00:05:41,460 --> 00:05:44,680
Mr. Shirosaki may be able to join us if he's free after that.

91
00:05:44,680 --> 00:05:46,470
Sorry, but I'll pass.

92
00:05:46,470 --> 00:05:48,440
- What?
- Come on, join us.

93
00:05:48,440 --> 00:05:50,010
Everyone, please go ahead.

94
00:05:50,010 --> 00:05:51,760
- Don't be shy.
- I also have Sakura to look after.

95
00:05:51,760 --> 00:05:54,910
Just for a while, a while.

96
00:05:54,910 --> 00:05:56,520
- I'm so looking forward to it.
- Yeah.

97
00:05:56,520 --> 00:05:59,820
[Renovation of Block B, Animal Shelter Sincere Home
- Request for Urgent Support]

98
00:06:01,100 --> 00:06:04,170
Is that so? A donation?

99
00:06:04,170 --> 00:06:07,080
You and Kai have been working hard for this.

100
00:06:07,080 --> 00:06:08,870
I'm happy for you two.

101
00:06:08,870 --> 00:06:11,200
Perhaps you can drop by for a visit too, So Ha.

102
00:06:11,200 --> 00:06:15,380
She's right. You can go have a look.

103
00:06:17,850 --> 00:06:22,960
Say, why don't you invite Kai and Aiko to join you?

104
00:06:26,580 --> 00:06:28,070
A visit?

105
00:06:28,070 --> 00:06:30,270
These are the meeting minutes.

106
00:06:30,270 --> 00:06:35,010
And I'll take this and submit it to court tomorrow.

107
00:06:35,670 --> 00:06:38,580
A visit, you said? To where?

108
00:06:38,580 --> 00:06:39,850
The animal shelter.

109
00:06:39,850 --> 00:06:45,130
So Ha suggested we go together
the next time Shirosaki visits.

110
00:06:45,130 --> 00:06:47,120
Now that you mention it,

111
00:06:47,120 --> 00:06:51,340
I hear there's been a rise in issues
with previous owners of adopted pets.

112
00:06:51,340 --> 00:06:56,040
Right. Shirosaki isn't familiar with legal matters,
so I've been asked to help.

113
00:07:00,550 --> 00:07:06,480
Say, has there been any progress since then?

114
00:07:07,220 --> 00:07:08,550
What progress?

115
00:07:08,550 --> 00:07:12,780
With Mr. Shirosaki... or perhaps with Mr. So Ha?

116
00:07:13,980 --> 00:07:22,510
I can tell that problems have been coming to you
in waves lately.

117
00:07:28,470 --> 00:07:34,420
By "progress"... what do you mean?

118
00:07:35,720 --> 00:07:38,060
- Sorry?
- In fact, I need your advice.

119
00:07:38,060 --> 00:07:42,400
In love, how do you define "progress"?

120
00:07:45,160 --> 00:07:47,790
Let's see...

121
00:07:49,030 --> 00:07:54,120
First, you'd go out for meals,
and ascertain your feelings for one another.

122
00:07:54,120 --> 00:08:00,290
Then meals become dates,
and you'd grow closer from there.

123
00:08:01,310 --> 00:08:04,140
Better not to do things in the wrong order though.

124
00:08:04,140 --> 00:08:09,530
- Wrong order?
- For example, if you suddenly get physical and cross the line,

125
00:08:10,460 --> 00:08:12,910
things usually won't go well.

126
00:08:22,900 --> 00:08:27,750
If that's the case... it's too late.

127
00:08:42,240 --> 00:08:44,930
What's wrong, Shogun?

128
00:08:53,270 --> 00:08:55,580
Alcohol so early in the morning?

129
00:08:56,250 --> 00:08:59,260
I wasn't drinking it.

130
00:08:59,260 --> 00:09:04,320
I was holding it, thinking it'd be great if I could drink it
at a time like this.

131
00:09:08,250 --> 00:09:10,200
Nah, scrap that idea.

132
00:09:10,970 --> 00:09:12,590
Kai.

133
00:09:16,400 --> 00:09:17,950
So Ha.

134
00:09:43,200 --> 00:09:46,800
I get it. It's about Aiko?

135
00:09:49,080 --> 00:09:52,110
The confession of love?

136
00:09:57,490 --> 00:09:59,250
You kissed?

137
00:09:59,250 --> 00:10:01,420
How did you know?

138
00:10:02,650 --> 00:10:05,380
Intuition like this goes beyond words.

139
00:10:05,380 --> 00:10:08,850
Wow... Wait, but she said it was just a reflex.

140
00:10:08,850 --> 00:10:11,890
You know, like what parrots and dolphins do...

141
00:10:13,360 --> 00:10:19,200
That was what she told me, but I don't quite get it.

142
00:10:20,310 --> 00:10:21,950
Reflex?

143
00:10:25,480 --> 00:10:28,080
You two are really dull.

144
00:10:28,080 --> 00:10:30,340
What?

145
00:10:30,340 --> 00:10:33,170
What do you want to do, Kai?

146
00:10:33,170 --> 00:10:36,430
What do I want to do?

147
00:10:44,260 --> 00:10:46,530
Delete it.

148
00:10:46,530 --> 00:10:49,000
Erase that memory.

149
00:10:49,000 --> 00:10:52,070
Nothing. Nothing happened at all.

150
00:10:57,540 --> 00:10:59,600
I'll shelve that for now.

151
00:11:00,190 --> 00:11:03,030
Things will go back to normal once the dust settles.

152
00:11:03,030 --> 00:11:06,850
That's it. Just shelve it for now.

153
00:11:09,150 --> 00:11:12,030
These two are really...

154
00:11:14,270 --> 00:11:19,260
Shogun, what do you think we should do?

155
00:11:24,690 --> 00:11:27,360
I've got an idea.

156
00:11:29,800 --> 00:11:34,840
I have to do something about this. For the two of them.

157
00:11:42,030 --> 00:11:45,000
[Episode 8]

158
00:11:53,370 --> 00:11:55,220
Thanks.

159
00:11:56,260 --> 00:11:58,570
Hey there, Aiko.

160
00:11:58,570 --> 00:12:02,230
- For you.
- Thank you.

161
00:12:02,230 --> 00:12:06,020
It's our first outdoor trip together.

162
00:12:06,020 --> 00:12:07,380
Let's take a picture.

163
00:12:07,380 --> 00:12:08,780
What?

164
00:12:13,750 --> 00:12:15,360
Sorry.

165
00:12:16,490 --> 00:12:18,960
Come closer.

166
00:12:18,960 --> 00:12:23,120
Ready, say cheese.

167
00:12:25,740 --> 00:12:27,590
Looks good.

168
00:12:27,590 --> 00:12:28,780
Let's go, shall we?

169
00:12:28,780 --> 00:12:30,140
Sure.

170
00:12:33,970 --> 00:12:38,090
Aiko, thanks for offering to take over the wheel.

171
00:12:38,090 --> 00:12:40,800
No problem. I like driving anyway.

172
00:12:53,760 --> 00:12:56,010
What kind of place is this animal shelter?

173
00:12:56,010 --> 00:13:01,990
Well, Sincere Home is an NPO that's run by the former principal
[NPO: Non-profit organization]

174
00:13:01,990 --> 00:13:05,870
of the pet grooming school that Yuka graduated from.

175
00:13:05,870 --> 00:13:09,990
Wow, I'm excited to visit the place. Let's go!

176
00:13:17,940 --> 00:13:22,170
First, they take in dogs and cats
from the municipal animal welfare center.

177
00:13:22,170 --> 00:13:26,860
The animals are then isolated for a week for medical tests,
before being moved to the housing unit.

178
00:13:26,860 --> 00:13:28,510
How many animals are you currently sheltering?

179
00:13:28,510 --> 00:13:31,780
We have up to 80 animals, dogs and cats included.

180
00:13:31,780 --> 00:13:33,040
Would you like to look around?

181
00:13:33,040 --> 00:13:35,090
Yes, please.

182
00:13:35,090 --> 00:13:37,380
Kai, go with them.

183
00:13:37,380 --> 00:13:39,660
- I'll stay to...
- No.

184
00:13:39,660 --> 00:13:43,420
He has work to do. You and I will go, So Ha.

185
00:13:44,170 --> 00:13:45,870
Let's go, So Ha.

186
00:13:57,340 --> 00:14:01,210
Here is where they're trained to socialize and get used to people.

187
00:14:01,210 --> 00:14:03,300
To teach them proper behavior.

188
00:14:03,300 --> 00:14:06,730
But that doesn't mean these dogs haven't been trained.

189
00:14:06,730 --> 00:14:09,550
There's always a reason for their inappropriate behavior.

190
00:14:09,550 --> 00:14:15,620
Not enough food, lacking sleep -
it could even stem from a fear of humans.

191
00:14:15,620 --> 00:14:19,930
So these trainers try to find out the reason,
and improve their behavior, right?

192
00:14:21,810 --> 00:14:23,460
The scenery here is beautiful.

193
00:14:23,460 --> 00:14:27,070
You can get a better view of the scenery further up ahead.

194
00:14:39,000 --> 00:14:43,030
I'll let those two take it from here.

195
00:14:59,940 --> 00:15:01,840
Shall we?

196
00:15:04,830 --> 00:15:06,330
Ready?

197
00:15:06,330 --> 00:15:08,950
One, two, say cheese.

198
00:15:08,950 --> 00:15:11,650
It's done. Thank you.

199
00:15:17,270 --> 00:15:20,440
Shogun totally loves this place.

200
00:15:20,440 --> 00:15:22,650
He runs around forever whenever I bring him here.

201
00:15:22,650 --> 00:15:25,390
Maybe next time I'll bring Sakura here, too.

202
00:15:49,670 --> 00:15:56,410
I guess... I still can't erase that from my memory.

203
00:15:57,200 --> 00:15:58,680
What?

204
00:15:59,400 --> 00:16:03,490
I mean, that reflex thing...

205
00:16:03,490 --> 00:16:06,410
Don't worry, I thought nothing of it.

206
00:16:06,410 --> 00:16:08,680
- "Nothing"?
- Well...

207
00:16:08,680 --> 00:16:11,770
Nothing strange, that is.

208
00:16:11,770 --> 00:16:13,340
Even though we kissed?

209
00:16:13,340 --> 00:16:15,950
To be more specific, the one who kissed me, was you...

210
00:16:15,950 --> 00:16:19,780
To be even more specific,
the one who first came over and touched my hair, was you.

211
00:16:19,780 --> 00:16:21,410
That's because a leaf was...

212
00:16:21,410 --> 00:16:24,890
- A leaf?
- Yeah, a leaf. It was on your hair.

213
00:16:24,890 --> 00:16:27,080
The trees by the road... were they camphor trees?

214
00:16:27,080 --> 00:16:29,830
- We can go verify it if you want.
- Forget it.

215
00:16:32,200 --> 00:16:35,020
I thought nothing of it myself.

216
00:16:39,390 --> 00:16:41,460
If you'll excuse me.

217
00:16:41,460 --> 00:16:45,870
I just... wanted to properly talk to you...

218
00:16:52,590 --> 00:16:54,590
Nice breeze.

219
00:17:09,650 --> 00:17:11,370
We're done talking.

220
00:17:11,370 --> 00:17:15,040
We're not done, but if you say we're done, then we're done.

221
00:17:17,660 --> 00:17:21,100
What's going on, you two?

222
00:17:26,820 --> 00:17:28,180
Hello?

223
00:17:28,900 --> 00:17:31,490
Ruby? Of course I remember her.

224
00:17:33,370 --> 00:17:34,930
A misdiagnosis?

225
00:17:39,830 --> 00:17:41,090
[Shirosaki Animal Hospital]

226
00:17:41,090 --> 00:17:45,250
What do you mean by a misdiagnosis?

227
00:17:45,250 --> 00:17:47,820
If I remember correctly, your diagnosis for Ruby was...

228
00:17:47,820 --> 00:17:49,060
Glaucoma?

229
00:17:49,060 --> 00:17:51,470
It's likely primary glaucoma.

230
00:17:51,470 --> 00:17:56,090
We need to keep her eye pressure under control,
so please bring her in again in three days.

231
00:17:56,090 --> 00:17:59,610
But later on, Ruby's appetite began to dwindle.

232
00:17:59,610 --> 00:18:04,440
So I brought her to another hospital for a second opinion.
Turns out it was uveitis.

233
00:18:05,150 --> 00:18:07,140
Uveitis?
[inflammation of the uvea in the eye]

234
00:18:07,740 --> 00:18:12,220
And apparently, it was caused by lymphoma.

235
00:18:13,370 --> 00:18:15,240
How is Ruby's current condition?

236
00:18:15,240 --> 00:18:18,400
She's scheduled to undergo chemotherapy at this hospital.
[Doctor's Note]

237
00:18:18,400 --> 00:18:19,970
I see.

238
00:18:19,970 --> 00:18:22,720
But when I examined her,
I only found her eye pressure to be high.

239
00:18:22,720 --> 00:18:25,550
- There were no symptoms to suggest it was uveitis.
- So you're saying...

240
00:18:25,550 --> 00:18:29,160
that you're not responsible for this?

241
00:18:33,150 --> 00:18:37,120
Sir, I was also present when Mr. Shirosaki was examining Ruby.

242
00:18:37,120 --> 00:18:42,080
Ruby was in good health, her appetite was great,
and she didn't present any other symptoms.

243
00:18:42,080 --> 00:18:44,130
I'm suing this hospital.

244
00:18:45,020 --> 00:18:49,480
- Pardon?
- This dog is very popular, you see.

245
00:18:49,480 --> 00:18:55,700
She had ongoing contracts, several of which I had to reject
because of your misdiagnosis.

246
00:18:55,700 --> 00:18:59,090
I have to seek compensation for that loss of income.

247
00:18:59,090 --> 00:19:00,820
Sir, please...

248
00:19:02,410 --> 00:19:04,780
May I say something?

249
00:19:05,490 --> 00:19:07,860
Who are you?

250
00:19:07,860 --> 00:19:09,820
I am a lawyer.

251
00:19:11,490 --> 00:19:17,080
If you wish to seek compensation due to misdiagnosis,
you will need to present objective evidence.

252
00:19:17,080 --> 00:19:21,430
And it is your responsibility as the pet's owner,
to find that evidence.

253
00:19:22,720 --> 00:19:26,750
To ensure the case is handled based on fact and not emotion,

254
00:19:26,750 --> 00:19:30,630
you should first prepare evidence,

255
00:19:30,630 --> 00:19:35,680
and then use that as a basis for further discussion.

256
00:19:37,320 --> 00:19:40,500
We can provide you with the test results
and medical records from the consultation.

257
00:19:40,500 --> 00:19:42,350
You may also wish to get a third opinion from another doctor.

258
00:19:42,350 --> 00:19:45,050
Of course. That's what I plan to do.

259
00:19:45,050 --> 00:19:47,420
- Prepare the documents.
- Got it.

260
00:19:49,380 --> 00:19:51,900
Ruby, let's go.

261
00:20:07,300 --> 00:20:09,030
I'm home.

262
00:20:09,030 --> 00:20:10,270
Welcome back.

263
00:20:10,270 --> 00:20:11,760
Wow, looks delicious.

264
00:20:11,760 --> 00:20:15,850
I've put a lot of effort into today's dinner, so I guarantee it's good.

265
00:20:18,280 --> 00:20:22,780
Oh, right. Look what I bought.

266
00:20:22,780 --> 00:20:24,760
Ta-da.

267
00:20:24,760 --> 00:20:29,370
Are you perhaps worried about me?

268
00:20:31,350 --> 00:20:34,040
I've got the customer's complaint under control.

269
00:20:34,040 --> 00:20:37,270
I'm sure he'll understand with a proper explanation.

270
00:20:37,270 --> 00:20:39,770
I'm putting them in the fridge for now.

271
00:20:39,770 --> 00:20:42,470
Are you even listening?

272
00:20:42,470 --> 00:20:44,730
I'm not worried.

273
00:20:44,730 --> 00:20:48,680
You have Aiko as your guardian lawyer watching out for you.

274
00:20:56,250 --> 00:20:58,210
So Ha.

275
00:20:58,210 --> 00:21:00,990
And you too, Shogun.

276
00:21:02,220 --> 00:21:06,990
Whatever happens outside doesn't feel like a problem anymore

277
00:21:06,990 --> 00:21:09,830
once I think about having to make dinner for you guys at home.

278
00:21:09,830 --> 00:21:13,120
He's doing it again, making things all emotional.

279
00:21:15,310 --> 00:21:17,630
It's great to be able to work.

280
00:21:17,630 --> 00:21:19,510
What?

281
00:21:19,510 --> 00:21:22,630
Of course, work is tough.

282
00:21:22,630 --> 00:21:26,430
But that's precisely why you are able to help these animals.

283
00:21:26,430 --> 00:21:31,850
That's what I think whenever I see you,
Aiko, and Ms. Yuka doing your best.

284
00:21:34,710 --> 00:21:37,300
What can I do to help?

285
00:21:41,660 --> 00:21:44,960
You've grown up, So Ha.

286
00:21:44,960 --> 00:21:49,710
- You think so?
- I used to think you were only a super spoiled, rich kid.

287
00:21:49,710 --> 00:21:51,650
I take that as an insult.

288
00:21:51,650 --> 00:21:54,180
Alright, let's eat.

289
00:21:54,180 --> 00:21:57,780
- I'm digging in.
- Bon appétit.

290
00:21:59,770 --> 00:22:02,610
- Delish.
- Delish indeed.

291
00:22:02,610 --> 00:22:04,900
I knew your cooking would be amazing.

292
00:22:17,240 --> 00:22:20,120
- Here you go.
- Thank you.

293
00:22:20,120 --> 00:22:25,210
These are the documents
pertaining to pet-related lawsuit cases.

294
00:22:25,210 --> 00:22:26,460
Thanks for your help.

295
00:22:26,460 --> 00:22:31,150
That said, our firm doesn't often handle misdiagnosis cases.

296
00:22:31,150 --> 00:22:36,590
Most of these cases involve pet traffic accidents,
pet-biting, or animal trafficking.

297
00:22:36,590 --> 00:22:39,640
I'll be sure to look thoroughly into them regardless.

298
00:22:41,340 --> 00:22:47,050
Shirosaki finally found a sponsor,
and his dream is within reach.

299
00:22:47,050 --> 00:22:49,180
If things get complicated,

300
00:22:49,180 --> 00:22:54,840
everyone's efforts in helping these dogs and cats will all go to waste.

301
00:22:54,840 --> 00:22:57,480
That's the one thing I don't want to see happen.

302
00:23:02,510 --> 00:23:07,570
Oh, right. Mr. Kusakabe has handled several medical lawsuits.

303
00:23:07,570 --> 00:23:10,300
Perhaps he can provide some insight.

304
00:23:10,300 --> 00:23:13,080
- Has he gone home?
- No.

305
00:23:13,680 --> 00:23:17,030
He said he was dropping by here to, "replenish our stock".

306
00:23:18,590 --> 00:23:20,530
[La douce joie]

307
00:23:29,300 --> 00:23:31,540
This should be the place.

308
00:23:58,330 --> 00:24:00,280
Sagara was there?

309
00:24:00,280 --> 00:24:04,040
Yes. For some reason, he was with my boss.

310
00:24:05,030 --> 00:24:07,450
That Sagara?

311
00:24:07,450 --> 00:24:10,620
I ask that you sell Shirosaki Animal Hospital to me.

312
00:24:14,930 --> 00:24:20,120
I'm not sure what their meeting was for,
but just wanted to give you a heads up.

313
00:24:20,120 --> 00:24:22,240
Thank you for letting me know.

314
00:24:24,900 --> 00:24:29,700
Sir, we have an envelope from a legal courier.

315
00:24:31,450 --> 00:24:33,470
What's that?

316
00:24:33,470 --> 00:24:37,460
Could this be from Ruby's owner?
[Yokohama District Court]

317
00:24:49,270 --> 00:24:50,680
May I have a look?

318
00:24:50,680 --> 00:24:52,380
Sure.

319
00:24:56,680 --> 00:24:59,550
[Formal Complaint]

320
00:24:59,550 --> 00:25:02,140
It's a formal complaint.

321
00:25:02,140 --> 00:25:03,980
Formal complaint?

322
00:25:16,340 --> 00:25:18,340
The connection between these three people?

323
00:25:18,340 --> 00:25:21,360
Help me figure it out. Report anything, no matter how trivial.

324
00:25:21,360 --> 00:25:22,610
Understood.

325
00:25:22,610 --> 00:25:25,390
- Here you go.
- Thank you.

326
00:25:25,390 --> 00:25:28,010
Ms. Yuka, look.

327
00:25:28,010 --> 00:25:30,130
Someone just posted this.

328
00:25:34,700 --> 00:25:37,380
What the heck is this?
[Worst service ever]

329
00:25:37,380 --> 00:25:41,290
Did Ruby's owner do this?
[They're too much!] [Not going there anymore]

330
00:25:41,290 --> 00:25:44,030
It's strange that all these negative reviews came in so suddenly.

331
00:25:44,030 --> 00:25:48,580
We can only ignore them. There's nothing for us to hide anyway.

332
00:25:57,340 --> 00:25:58,470
Sorry to interrupt.

333
00:25:58,470 --> 00:26:00,950
Take a look at this.

334
00:26:02,430 --> 00:26:06,620
This is the man who sued Shirosaki's hospital.

335
00:26:06,620 --> 00:26:09,240
The clinic he went to... belongs to Sagara.

336
00:26:12,080 --> 00:26:15,510
This is a list of customers who visited that clinic
in recent months.

337
00:26:16,490 --> 00:26:18,020
Take a look.

338
00:26:18,020 --> 00:26:19,770
You managed to get your hands on this?
[Visitor List - August 2025]

339
00:26:19,770 --> 00:26:24,440
I once covered for a mistake their receptionist made,
so she returned the favor.

340
00:26:31,130 --> 00:26:34,780
Found him.
[Attended by: Director, Gaku Sagara]

341
00:26:34,780 --> 00:26:36,980
[Visitor: Keita Honzawa]

342
00:26:36,980 --> 00:26:39,700
He had met up with our chief.

343
00:26:40,550 --> 00:26:43,510
[Attended by: Director, Gaku Sagara]
[Visitor: Keita Honzawa]

344
00:26:43,510 --> 00:26:46,000
[Olu'Olu Clinic]

345
00:26:46,000 --> 00:26:48,560
How are the three of them connected?

346
00:26:49,190 --> 00:26:51,010
[Shirosaki Animal Hospital]

347
00:26:55,050 --> 00:26:57,270
Sorry, our morning consultations have ended.

348
00:26:57,270 --> 00:26:59,860
May we speak with your director?

349
00:27:03,540 --> 00:27:06,100
[Hisayo Koyanagi,
Ministry of Agriculture, Forestry and Fisheries]

350
00:27:06,100 --> 00:27:08,250
Ministry of Agriculture?

351
00:27:09,160 --> 00:27:11,710
- Nefachin?
- Yes.

352
00:27:11,710 --> 00:27:16,900
It's an unapproved treatment for feline AIDS, or FIV.
We suspect you're utilizing this substance.

353
00:27:16,900 --> 00:27:18,860
No, our hospital uses no such thing.

354
00:27:18,860 --> 00:27:20,620
- We've received report that you do.
- From who?

355
00:27:20,620 --> 00:27:23,550
I'm not legally authorized to disclose that.

356
00:27:23,550 --> 00:27:29,410
We only utilize standard symptomatic treatments
like steroids, antibiotics, and analgesic drugs.

357
00:27:29,410 --> 00:27:31,000
Then what's this?

358
00:27:32,800 --> 00:27:35,380
[Nefachin]

359
00:27:39,420 --> 00:27:40,970
Young master.

360
00:27:40,970 --> 00:27:42,480
How did it go?

361
00:27:42,480 --> 00:27:48,910
After some investigating,
it seems this matter is related to us after all.

362
00:27:48,910 --> 00:27:50,360
What?

363
00:27:51,170 --> 00:27:56,720
The whole thing started with WooRoA Logistics,
where you used to work, and their strategy in Asia.

364
00:27:57,570 --> 00:28:00,900
If I recall correctly, they wanted to expand WooRoA Electronics.

365
00:28:00,900 --> 00:28:04,030
With that expansion,

366
00:28:04,030 --> 00:28:11,230
they plan to set up logistics hubs
in Tokyo, Dalian, Mumbai, and Kuala Lumpur.

367
00:28:11,230 --> 00:28:15,420
And if we can become the legal counsel
for the entire logistics arm of WooRoA...

368
00:28:15,420 --> 00:28:19,570
Our firm, in name and in reality,

369
00:28:19,570 --> 00:28:24,880
will undoubtedly become a major firm. Boom!

370
00:28:24,880 --> 00:28:28,170
Major firm...

371
00:28:28,170 --> 00:28:32,270
To gain favor with WooRoA, the one they are targeting...

372
00:28:32,270 --> 00:28:34,650
is you, Young Master.

373
00:28:34,650 --> 00:28:40,030
They teamed up with that Sagara to ruin Mr. Kai's reputation,
and get him into financial trouble.

374
00:28:41,050 --> 00:28:45,250
Sir, staying with Mr. Kai will hurt him further.

375
00:28:45,250 --> 00:28:47,430
You have no choice but to return to Seoul.

376
00:28:49,510 --> 00:28:51,430
This is all because of me.

377
00:28:56,000 --> 00:28:58,930
- Where is Sagara's clinic?
- Huh?

378
00:28:58,930 --> 00:29:01,310
I want to meet him.

379
00:29:01,310 --> 00:29:02,940
Young Master...

380
00:29:05,140 --> 00:29:06,930
Sir...

381
00:29:08,340 --> 00:29:11,870
I have never handled that drug before.

382
00:29:11,870 --> 00:29:16,300
Got it. That's all. Thank you for your time.

383
00:29:16,300 --> 00:29:18,400
Thank you.

384
00:29:19,220 --> 00:29:23,170
Indeed, we did not find any signs of Nefachin being used.

385
00:29:23,170 --> 00:29:25,870
I am glad that you understand.

386
00:29:25,870 --> 00:29:28,230
We will visit again.

387
00:29:46,830 --> 00:29:50,930
It's a great honor to have you gracing my clinic,

388
00:29:50,930 --> 00:29:54,360
WooRoA Group's Mr. Woo So Ha.

389
00:29:54,920 --> 00:29:57,140
An honor?

390
00:29:57,140 --> 00:29:59,070
I'm just a nobody right now.

391
00:29:59,070 --> 00:30:03,440
But very soon, you will become somebody.

392
00:30:05,400 --> 00:30:07,350
It was you, right?

393
00:30:07,990 --> 00:30:13,660
You were scheming behind Kai's back and had him cornered.

394
00:30:13,660 --> 00:30:17,050
Hang on a second. What are you talking about?

395
00:30:19,860 --> 00:30:22,740
The way you accuse me like this...

396
00:30:22,740 --> 00:30:27,990
I wanted to help Kai, but he was the one who rejected my help.

397
00:30:29,720 --> 00:30:33,170
Besides, do you have any evidence?

398
00:30:33,170 --> 00:30:35,170
- Evidence?
- That's right.

399
00:30:35,170 --> 00:30:39,480
Don't worry, I'll find it very soon.

400
00:30:39,480 --> 00:30:43,000
Because you're the heir to WooRoA?

401
00:30:46,180 --> 00:30:51,220
But as I recall, right now, you're simply Woo So Ha,
the man who ran away from home, no?

402
00:30:54,470 --> 00:31:01,150
You used the dog and Kai as an excuse
to run away from WooRoA.

403
00:31:01,150 --> 00:31:05,060
Sure, you are savoring your freedom,

404
00:31:05,060 --> 00:31:09,520
but ultimately, you are nothing.

405
00:31:10,490 --> 00:31:12,020
What do you know about me?

406
00:31:12,020 --> 00:31:14,990
That's why you have been used.

407
00:31:19,200 --> 00:31:23,060
Let me ask you again. What are you here for?

408
00:31:30,240 --> 00:31:34,180
It's about time to end your vacation.

409
00:31:34,180 --> 00:31:36,460
I'm worried about Kai.

410
00:31:52,060 --> 00:31:55,100
Hello, Shirosaki Animal Hospital.

411
00:31:55,100 --> 00:31:58,320
Sure, you wish to cancel your appointment?

412
00:31:58,320 --> 00:32:00,460
Noted.

413
00:32:00,460 --> 00:32:02,450
Have a good day.

414
00:32:02,450 --> 00:32:04,380
Goodbye.

415
00:32:12,020 --> 00:32:14,560
Kosuke.

416
00:32:14,560 --> 00:32:17,600
I heard the folks from the Ministry of Agriculture came?

417
00:32:20,690 --> 00:32:24,800
Why is Sagara doing this to Mr. Shirosaki?

418
00:32:25,430 --> 00:32:26,780
What?

419
00:32:26,780 --> 00:32:31,070
I finally understand what you meant.

420
00:32:31,820 --> 00:32:35,510
My capacity for love now is only this big.

421
00:32:36,410 --> 00:32:39,450
My head's full with this hospital's problems.

422
00:32:43,570 --> 00:32:47,140
I won't disturb you anymore.

423
00:33:01,560 --> 00:33:03,410
Ms. Hanamura.

424
00:33:03,410 --> 00:33:05,290
Yes?

425
00:33:05,290 --> 00:33:09,170
I have a friend, the CEO of an apparel company.
He's having problems with his divorce.

426
00:33:09,170 --> 00:33:12,090
I'm introducing you to him. Please advise him on what to do.

427
00:33:12,090 --> 00:33:14,770
Yes, sir. My pleasure.

428
00:33:14,770 --> 00:33:21,050
That means no more playing detective.

429
00:33:21,870 --> 00:33:25,100
Don't underestimate my network of informants.

430
00:33:28,120 --> 00:33:30,770
I'm sorry, sir. But there's something bothering me...

431
00:33:30,770 --> 00:33:35,590
This... is my final warning.

432
00:33:37,680 --> 00:33:41,790
Just focus on your work.

433
00:33:54,150 --> 00:33:57,090
[Notice of Temporary Closure]
[Thank you for supporting Shirosaki Animal Hospital...]

434
00:34:01,110 --> 00:34:03,940
[A warm place for every living being]

435
00:34:14,510 --> 00:34:16,950
Long time no see, Mr. Shirosaki.

436
00:34:16,950 --> 00:34:18,710
Ah, that's...

437
00:34:18,710 --> 00:34:22,610
This is my Chiru-chiru. I brought her here for grooming.

438
00:34:22,610 --> 00:34:25,690
- Come on, greet Mr. Shirosaki.
- She's adorable.

439
00:34:26,960 --> 00:34:29,110
That's it. That feeling.

440
00:34:32,530 --> 00:34:34,740
"These furkids are adorable."

441
00:34:34,740 --> 00:34:38,010
You'll be just fine if you keep feeling that way.

442
00:34:39,780 --> 00:34:43,440
Sir, thank you for your hard work every day.

443
00:34:43,440 --> 00:34:45,250
This may not be much, but...

444
00:34:45,250 --> 00:34:46,920
Now's the time for some eye care.

445
00:34:46,920 --> 00:34:48,350
Please cheer up.

446
00:34:48,350 --> 00:34:50,260
Please use this to heal your body.

447
00:34:50,260 --> 00:34:53,000
Thank you for always taking care of us.

448
00:34:54,040 --> 00:34:56,080
Ta-da!

449
00:34:56,080 --> 00:34:57,510
[Please cheer up. Hang in there]

450
00:34:57,510 --> 00:35:00,180
We'll follow you wherever you go, Mr. Shirosaki.

451
00:35:00,770 --> 00:35:02,730
That's right.

452
00:35:02,730 --> 00:35:07,170
That's great. Thank you, that's wonderful.

453
00:35:07,170 --> 00:35:09,580
How old is Chiru-chiru?

454
00:35:09,580 --> 00:35:12,860
She's already ten years old. A full-grown lady.

455
00:35:12,860 --> 00:35:16,090
Quite the seductress, huh? Both Chiru-chiru and Michiru.

456
00:35:16,090 --> 00:35:19,120
Well, we get that often.

457
00:35:20,150 --> 00:35:21,930
What's with that all of a sudden?

458
00:35:21,930 --> 00:35:24,720
Right, let me massage your shoulders, Mr. Shirosaki!

459
00:35:24,720 --> 00:35:26,250
- What are you doing?
- Hurry, Natsuki!

460
00:35:26,250 --> 00:35:27,770
Don't massage too hard.

461
00:35:27,770 --> 00:35:29,590
Why does he need two of you to do it?

462
00:35:29,590 --> 00:35:33,390
- My left shoulder is...
- Balance it, balance it.

463
00:35:47,400 --> 00:35:49,720
The whole thing started with WooRoA Logistics,

464
00:35:49,720 --> 00:35:52,470
where you used to work, and their strategy in Asia.

465
00:35:52,470 --> 00:35:58,450
To gain favor with WooRoA, the one they are targeting,
is you, Young master.

466
00:35:58,450 --> 00:36:00,550
This is all because of me.

467
00:36:00,550 --> 00:36:04,550
Ms. Yuka, look. Someone just posted this.

468
00:36:04,550 --> 00:36:06,530
Could this be from Ruby's owner?

469
00:36:06,530 --> 00:36:08,180
It's a formal complaint.
[Formal Complaint]

470
00:36:08,180 --> 00:36:09,460
Formal complaint?

471
00:36:09,460 --> 00:36:12,810
It's about time to end your vacation.

472
00:36:12,810 --> 00:36:15,070
I'm worried about Kai.

473
00:36:37,970 --> 00:36:39,670
It's you, Aiko.

474
00:36:41,710 --> 00:36:43,490
Please, come in.

475
00:36:44,720 --> 00:36:46,590
Sorry to disturb you.

476
00:36:50,460 --> 00:36:52,530
Thank you.

477
00:36:53,280 --> 00:36:55,660
You came to see Kai?

478
00:37:00,640 --> 00:37:04,630
There's something going on.

479
00:37:05,440 --> 00:37:08,250
I don't have any proof of it yet,

480
00:37:08,910 --> 00:37:13,410
but someone is trying to force Shirosaki into a corner.

481
00:37:20,800 --> 00:37:23,390
I came here to discuss that matter.

482
00:37:27,220 --> 00:37:29,250
It's all my fault.

483
00:37:30,040 --> 00:37:31,710
I'm sorry.

484
00:37:35,550 --> 00:37:38,300
I came here in search of Shogun.

485
00:37:39,100 --> 00:37:44,170
Then I met you and Kai.

486
00:37:45,840 --> 00:37:47,930
After spending time with one another...

487
00:37:51,000 --> 00:37:53,340
we became chingu.

488
00:37:56,380 --> 00:37:58,020
Thank you.

489
00:38:03,900 --> 00:38:07,270
What did you just say?

490
00:38:14,180 --> 00:38:15,860
I'm home.

491
00:38:25,180 --> 00:38:26,440
Welcome back.

492
00:38:26,440 --> 00:38:29,910
Sorry to disturb, Shirosaki.

493
00:38:30,820 --> 00:38:35,050
You came at the right time.
I have something to discuss with you.

494
00:38:38,520 --> 00:38:41,250
I'm only speaking hypothetically now, but...

495
00:38:43,130 --> 00:38:45,550
If I decide to sell the hospital,

496
00:38:45,550 --> 00:38:49,000
would you handle the negotiation on my behalf?

497
00:38:49,000 --> 00:38:50,480
Come again?

498
00:38:51,820 --> 00:38:57,200
It won't happen yet, but if the financial situation worsens
and becomes a burden to the staff,

499
00:38:57,200 --> 00:39:00,810
or affects the quality of care to the animals,

500
00:39:00,810 --> 00:39:03,660
then I have to make a decision.

501
00:39:06,370 --> 00:39:11,220
If I sell the hospital to Sagara,
the animal shelter will also be taken care of.

502
00:39:11,220 --> 00:39:16,280
- But...
- Of course, I want to keep the hospital if I can.

503
00:39:17,860 --> 00:39:20,830
But as its director,

504
00:39:20,830 --> 00:39:24,370
I have to also consider the possibility
of selling the hospital.

505
00:39:26,680 --> 00:39:31,120
If me stepping down can solve the problem, I will do so.

506
00:39:31,120 --> 00:39:32,980
You're a coward.

507
00:39:35,250 --> 00:39:40,610
My father always tells me
that we don't need any incompetent managers.

508
00:39:40,610 --> 00:39:42,400
So Ha, stop.

509
00:39:44,140 --> 00:39:47,370
You're running away.

510
00:39:47,370 --> 00:39:49,660
No, I'm not.

511
00:39:49,660 --> 00:39:52,140
I'm going back.

512
00:39:52,140 --> 00:39:55,050
- What?
- To Seoul.

513
00:39:57,330 --> 00:40:01,500
If I continue staying here, I'll become weak like you.

514
00:40:05,080 --> 00:40:08,640
In that case, be my guest.

515
00:40:08,640 --> 00:40:11,250
Yeah, I'll go back.

516
00:40:13,740 --> 00:40:15,670
I don't need this place anymore.

517
00:40:18,420 --> 00:40:20,920
I don't need anything, anymore.

518
00:40:24,080 --> 00:40:26,140
Wait, So Ha.

519
00:41:18,370 --> 00:41:20,750
Who cares about So Ha?

520
00:41:31,610 --> 00:41:36,040
Hey, I'm heading out first. I'll leave the keys to you.

521
00:41:43,730 --> 00:41:45,290
You awake?

522
00:42:13,630 --> 00:42:15,550
So Ha has left?

523
00:42:15,550 --> 00:42:17,550
I figured he'd contact you.

524
00:42:17,550 --> 00:42:20,570
I haven't heard from him either.

525
00:42:20,570 --> 00:42:23,190
So right now, he's probably...

526
00:42:24,540 --> 00:42:26,350
Then he meant it?

527
00:42:42,350 --> 00:42:46,330
♫♫

528
00:42:46,330 --> 00:42:51,670
♫♫

529
00:42:51,670 --> 00:42:56,640
♫♫

530
00:42:56,640 --> 00:43:01,210
♫♫

531
00:43:02,380 --> 00:43:07,350
♫♫

532
00:43:07,350 --> 00:43:11,980
♫♫

533
00:43:13,320 --> 00:43:15,640
- Did he pick up?
- No.

534
00:43:15,640 --> 00:43:16,890
This way.

535
00:43:16,890 --> 00:43:19,950
♫♫

536
00:43:22,720 --> 00:43:28,340
♫♫

537
00:43:28,340 --> 00:43:31,100
I didn't think he'd really leave.

538
00:43:33,380 --> 00:43:35,120
Let's go.

539
00:43:35,120 --> 00:43:36,530
What?

540
00:43:36,530 --> 00:43:39,500
We may never see him again.

541
00:43:39,500 --> 00:43:41,800
I don't want to have any regrets.

542
00:43:43,060 --> 00:43:47,550
- Go? Where?
- To see So Ha.

543
00:43:49,050 --> 00:43:50,680
In Seoul.

544
00:43:51,260 --> 00:43:55,980
♫♫

